<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c5"><SPAN CLASS="c6">Pittsfield: Church to host conversation on race</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c5"><SPAN CLASS="c7">SECTION: </SPAN><SPAN CLASS="c2">LOCAL</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c5"><SPAN CLASS="c7">LENGTH: </SPAN><SPAN CLASS="c2">121 words</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Tuesday July 30, 2013</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">In the wake of the death of Trayvon Martin and the outcome of the George Zimmerman trial, South Congregational Church, 110 South St., will host a community conversation from 6 to 8 p.m. on Thursday, Aug. 1. </SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">The organizers hope that it will lead to more collaborative work with sacred and secular community partners.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">This conversation on race seeks to open a different premise of racial awareness, whiteness, in order to move to a healthier and more just community environment for all people.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Clergy from South Congregational Church, St. Stephen's Episcopal Church, and First Baptist Church will facilitate. Pizza and salad will be served and a free-will offering to cover the cost of the food will be received.</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c5"><SPAN CLASS="c7">LOAD-DATE: </SPAN><SPAN CLASS="c2">July 31, 2013</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
